						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Dēvanāyagapperumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I) Year 31: 938 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged at the end. This inscription records a gift of ninety sheep for burning a perpetual lamp to the god of Tiruveyintirapuram by Vāṉavaṉmādēviyār, the daughter of the Pāṇḍyaṉ ruler, Rāsasiṅgaperumāṉār (Rājasiṁha).</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Āvaṇam.,</hi> No. 7 (1996) p. 21. </p>						

						</summary>
